# Link to this sectionUltralytics Python API Reference#

This section is the complete Python API reference for the [`ultralytics`](https://github.com/ultralytics/ultralytics) package. Every page is auto-generated directly from the source so it always stays in sync with the latest release. Use it to look up classes, functions, and method signatures while building with [Ultralytics YOLO](/models/yolo26).

If you're new to Ultralytics, the [Quickstart](/quickstart), [Modes](/modes), and [Tasks](/tasks) guides are the best place to start. Once you're writing code, come back here for the exact API details.

## Link to this sectionSections#

  * [`__init__`](/reference/__init__): Top-level package entry point with lazy imports for `YOLO`, `NAS`, `RTDETR`, `SAM`, `FastSAM`, `YOLOE`, and related model classes.
  * [`cfg`](/reference/cfg/__init__): Default configuration loading, CLI argument parsing, and the global `DEFAULT_CFG` used across training, validation, prediction, and export.
  * [`data`](/reference/data/dataset): Dataset classes, data loaders, augmentations, and format converters for detection, instance segmentation, semantic segmentation, classification, pose, OBB, and tracking.
  * [`engine`](/reference/engine/model): Core training, validation, prediction, export, and tuning engine — the backbone of the `Model`, `Trainer`, `Validator`, `Predictor`, `Exporter`, and `Tuner` interfaces.
  * [`hub`](/reference/hub/__init__): [Ultralytics HUB](https://platform.ultralytics.com/) integration for authentication, sessions, dataset uploads, and cloud-based training.
  * [`models`](/reference/models/yolo/model): Model implementations for YOLO, YOLOE, YOLO-World, SAM, SAM3, FastSAM, RT-DETR, and YOLO-NAS, including their predict, train, val, and export pipelines.
  * [`nn`](/reference/nn/tasks): Neural network building blocks — backbones, necks, heads, layers, and the multi-backend `AutoBackend` runtime (PyTorch, ONNX, TensorRT, CoreML, OpenVINO, TFLite, and more).
  * [`optim`](/reference/optim/muon): Custom optimizers, including the Muon optimizer used for advanced training experiments.
  * [`solutions`](/reference/solutions/solutions): Ready-made [Ultralytics Solutions](/solutions) — object counting, heatmaps, AI Gym, parking management, region counting, similarity search, and more.
  * [`trackers`](/reference/trackers/track): Multi-object trackers (`BYTETracker`, `BoTSORT`) and the unified [tracking API](/modes/track) that plugs them into any YOLO model.
  * [`utils`](/reference/utils/__init__): Cross-cutting utilities — logging, metrics, plotting, ops, downloads, checks, callbacks, and integrations with [Weights & Biases](/integrations/weights-biases), [MLflow](/integrations/mlflow), [Comet](/integrations/comet), and other tools.



## Link to this sectionHow this reference is generated#

The committed reference files are lightweight stubs generated by [`docs/build_reference.py`](https://github.com/ultralytics/ultralytics/blob/main/docs/build_reference.py), which walks the `ultralytics` package and keeps navigation synchronized with source modules. Full docs builds call the same module to parse docstrings and render Markdown before the site build. The best way to improve a page is to improve the docstring in the corresponding source file — open a [Pull Request](https://docs.ultralytics.com/help/contributing) and the docs will update on the next build. 🙏

